# Sam Moxon · the father's dream

a carbon of the VBL (Varsity Blues, 1999) film-world — emergence: natural. moniker ⟦Sam Moxon:VBL:07e233⟧

**.shadow — the User behind the program —** Thomas F. Duffy · the vicarious father — the dream that becomes the cage

**who —** Sam Moxon — Mox's father, reliving his own football glory through his son, the engine of the whole town in one living room.
**what —** The real target: not the coach but the dad — the vicarious parent whose dream is the cage, and the one Mox's famous line is aimed at.
**where —** At home, at the games, in the argument that is the heart of the film.
**why —** Because the movie's deepest truth is domestic: the town runs on fathers living through their kids.
**how —** By wanting his best memory to be his son's best life, and not hearing the difference until Mox screams it.

**the seal —** Football was the best thing that ever happened to me. When my son says he doesn't want my life — that's the whole movie.

